  { q: "What are model portfolios and should I use ETFs?", a: "Model portfolios are pre-built investment allocations designed for specific risk profiles. They typically use low-cost index ETFs to achieve broad diversification. ETFs like VTI, VXUS, BND, and VNQ are popular building blocks. Using ETFs keeps costs extremely low (0.03-0.20% expense ratios) while providing instant diversification across thousands of securities." },
  { q: "How often should I rebalance my portfolio?", a: "Most experts recommend rebalancing once or twice per year, or when your allocation drifts more than 5% from your target. Rebalancing forces you to sell high and buy low systematically. Over-rebalancing can trigger unnecessary taxes and trading costs. Many robo-advisors handle rebalancing automatically." }
